text: Gunther Kaschlun (9 February 1935 - 7 August 2020) was a West German rower. He represented the United Team of Germany. He competed at the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne with the men's coxless four where they were eliminated in the semi-final. He died in August 2020 at the age of 85.Zum Tod von Gunther Kaschlun ==References== Category:1935 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Olympians for Germany Category:German rowers
